- [Jimmy] Yes.
- Ladies, can we line up here?

32:57.967 --> 32:59.913
Let's just take one of each menus.

33:00.760 --> 33:02.830
I've got a plan for the food.

33:02.830 --> 33:06.000
Let's focus first on the menu
and plates for the restaurant.

33:06.000 --> 33:07.540
Let's start off at the beginning.

33:07.540 --> 33:09.750
French onion soup and a bowl of chilli.

33:09.750 --> 33:10.680
- [Jimmy] Oh, wow.

33:10.680 --> 33:12.756
- [Gordon] We got the beef
stroganoff with wild mushrooms.

33:12.756 --> 33:13.930
- [Jimmy] Oh, yeah.

33:13.930 --> 33:15.560
- Next to that, you got
the chicken Alfredo.

33:15.560 --> 33:16.980
- [Melody] I like that.

33:16.980 --> 33:20.030
- Let's focus on the big
menu for the wedding tonight.

33:20.030 --> 33:23.890
The perfect entre is
the braised short ribs.

33:23.890 --> 33:25.270
- [Marta] Oh, beautiful.

33:25.270 --> 33:26.730
- [Gordon] Next to that,
we got local walleye.

33:26.730 --> 33:27.563
- [Jimmy] That's amazing.

33:27.563 --> 33:28.490
- Beautifully seared.

33:28.490 --> 33:30.010
- Oh, look at that.

33:30.010 --> 33:31.420
Oh, that's beautiful.

33:31.420 --> 33:33.019
- Nothing complicated.

33:33.019 --> 33:35.224
- [Jimmy] And everything
looks so appetising, too.

33:35.224 --> 33:36.190
- [Gordon] Clean.

33:36.190 --> 33:37.260
- [Jimmy] Yes.

33:37.260 --> 33:40.070
- But there is one thing
missing, and that's a chef.

33:40.070 --> 33:42.710
So I've arranged for a unique person

33:42.710 --> 33:44.180
that has been working with me in Vegas

33:44.180 --> 33:45.350
for the last five years.

33:45.350 --> 33:48.402
She is incredible and she's
gonna be your consultant chef.

33:48.402 --> 33:49.330
- Okay.

33:49.330 --> 33:51.447
- Let me introduce you to Keisha.

33:51.447 --> 33:52.750
Good morning, my darling.

33:52.750 --> 33:54.106
Come stand over here, please.

33:54.106 --> 33:56.057
- Thank you. Nice to see you guys.

33:56.057 --> 33:59.080
- So, Marta, this young
lady knows her stuff.

33:59.080 --> 34:02.110
She's gonna help instal
somebody on a full-time basis.

34:02.110 --> 34:03.780
But the hand-over process

34:03.780 --> 34:05.450
is gonna be part of her responsibility.

34:05.450 --> 34:06.460
- [Marta] Are you excited, Grant?

34:06.460 --> 34:07.840
- Very, very excited.

34:07.840 --> 34:09.139
- Yay.
- [Gordon] Grant,

34:09.139 --> 34:10.330
work closely with her.

34:10.330 --> 34:11.163
- Absolutely.

34:11.163 --> 34:14.659
- Now, remember, tonight, you're
gonna step up and run this.

34:14.659 --> 34:16.650
The burden is now on your shoulders.

34:16.650 --> 34:18.174
- I'm prepared to take it.

34:18.174 --> 34:21.257
(gentle piano music)

34:23.245 --> 34:24.282
- Morning.
- Hello.

34:24.282 --> 34:25.201
- Hello, gorgeous.

34:25.201 --> 34:27.141
- Come on in.
- Morning, ladies.

34:27.141 --> 34:28.322
How are you? You look amazing.

34:28.322 --> 34:31.165
When I check in with Roxanne
and Eric to assure them

34:31.165 --> 34:32.753
that everything is on
track with their wedding.

34:32.753 --> 34:33.889
How are you feeling?

34:33.889 --> 34:34.723
- Very good.

34:34.723 --> 34:35.681
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

34:35.681 --> 34:36.514
- I just want to give you the heads up

34:36.514 --> 34:37.699
room's looking gorgeous.

34:38.639 --> 34:40.460
- Okay, now let's just set 'em up.

34:40.460 --> 34:41.980
- [Gordon] I put Jimmy
in charge of managing

34:41.980 --> 34:45.139
the entire event from the
ceremony to the reception.

34:45.139 --> 34:46.179
- [Jimmy] That's a cool layout.

34:46.179 --> 34:47.560
- [Melody] Isn't it pretty
